#
WHO

>> COMMAND
Lists the people currently in the game.
Some people may choose to remain unseen.

EXAMPLE :
	> who -n   - shows people with level <= n
	> who =n   - shows people with level == n
	> who +n   - got the idea?
	or
	> who  *   - for a list of people in the area (why * ??)
#
GIVE

>> COMMAND
If you feel benevolent, you may give some stuff to someone in need.

EXAMPLE :
	> give bread to the beggar
#
SAVE

>> COMMAND
Save your person. This includes experience points, strength, gold, etc.
Any equipment you may have gathered is also saved.
#
STRING

>> WIZ COMMAND
For changing the text-strings associated with objects and characters.
The format is : string <type> <name> <field> [<string> | <keyword>]

	type is either 'obj' or 'char'.
	field is one of the following (the names may be abbreviated) :
	name (the call-name of an obj/char - kill giant)
	short (for inventory lists (obj's) and actions (char's))
	long (for when obj/character is seen in room)
	title (for players)
	description (For look at. For obj's, must be followed by a keyword)
	delete-description (only for obj's. Must be followed by keyword)

Where a string is expected as the last argument, a newline will make you enter
a string mode, and the game will prompt you for new lines to the string until
you exceed the maximum length for the string or you end a line with a '@'.
#
LOAD

>> WIZ COMMAND
For loading new objects or characters from the database.
The format is : load <type> <number>

	type is either 'obj' or 'char'.
	number is the number of the object or character you wish to create.
