SAY TELL WHISPER SHOUT ASK GTELL SEND CHAT

>> COMMAND
If you consider communicating with other beings, you might be understood
better if you start your sentences with either say,tell,whisper or shout.

EXAMPLE :
	> say I'm a jerk
	> tell unclesam You're dead meat - sucker!

You can use ' as a shorthand for say.

gtell is abbreviation of group tell. if you gtell <something>, all your 
group will hear what you told.

Chat is abbreviation of MUD World. if you chat <something>, all player 
will hear what you told except nochat player.
you can chat even when you are sleeping, but.. if you want chat, then you
must get level higher than 15.  Good luck to you.
#
QUI SHUTDOW

>> COMMAND
Just to prevent accidental quittings and/or shutdowns.
This command doesn't DO anything, it simply is.
#
KILL HIT

>> COMMAND
A good way to start a fight.
#
KICK

>> SKILL : WARRIOR
The success of a kick depends upon how well you are learned and victim's ac.
The higher level you reach the harder you kick. There is one small catch -
whenever you kick (or miss) you will be unable to type any command for one
round of 'violence' - so be sure that you do not need to flee!
If your kick succeed and victim is player, then victim also unable to type
any command for one round. Damage is depends on your level.
If victim saves hit skill, damage will be half.

See also : RESCUE, BASH, MULTI KICK
#
"MULTI KICK"

>> SKILL : WARRIOR
Do some kicks against victim. This skill will decrease your movement.
Movement decreasing is depend on your level. You can't do anything for 1 round.
Damage depends on your level. If any kick succeed, victim also can't do anything
for 1 round. If victim saves hit skill, damage will be half.
#
BASH

>> SKILL : WARRIOR
The success of a bash depends upon how well you are learned. To bash someone
is to attempt to 'knock' that person over. If you succeed you will inflict
minor damage, and cause the victim to fall on it's rear. The victim will be
unable to issue any commands for 2 rounds of violence. If you miss you loose
your balance and fall.
A bash makes you unable to type commands for 2 rounds of violence.
Note that hitting a person who is resting/sitting will inflict 1.5 * damage.

See also : RESCUE, KICK, MULTI KICK
#
RESCUE

>> SKILL : WARRIOR
A rescue is an attempt to make a monster hit you instead of the person being
rescued. You can only 'turn' one monster for each attempt. This is highly
useable when playing in groups.
#
"DOUBLE ATTACK"

>> SKILL : MAGIC USER, CLERIC, THIEF, WARRIOR

With this skill, you can attack two times per one round.

See also : QUADRUPLE ATTACK
#
"QUADRUPLE ATTACK"

>> SKILL : MAGIC USER, CLERIC, THIEF, WARRIOR

With this skill, you can attack four times per one round.

See also : OCTA ATTACK
#
"OCTA ATTACK"

>> SKILL : WARRIOR

With this skill, you can attack eight times per one round.
#
"EXTRA DAMAGING"

>> SKILL : WARRIOR

Randomly, your damage is multiplied by 2. You will get more change, if you are
more learned.
#
STEAL

>> SKILL : THIEF
Use steal to steal gold or items from people. The chance of not getting
caught depends on how well you have practiced steal, and if the person
is asleep.

EXAMPLE :
	> steal gold drunk
#
BACKSTAB

>> SKILL : THIEF
Is a way to sneak up on a person, and attempt to place you dagger in his
back, at exactly the point where it does most damage. A successful backstab
gives a damage multiplier, depending on level.
The chance of successfully backstabbing a person depends on how well you
have practiced backstab and your level and dex.
You can always backstab sleeping persons.

See also : LIGHTNING MOVE
#
"LIGHTNING MOVE"

>> SKILL : THIEF

Thief can move like lightning during fight with this skill so monsters 
can't find who was hitting themselves. This skill make attacker stop fighting
this skill is useful for thief.

See also : BACKSTAB
#
FLASH

>> SKILL : THIEF

Thief can hit monster many time like a flash. All your move points will be used
for this skill.
Damage depends on your move points and level.
#
PARRY

>> SKILL : THIEF, WARRIOR
With this skill, you can parry when fighting.
#
DISARM

>> SKILL : THIEF, WARRIOR
With this skill, you can make victim's weapon unequiped.
#
"THROW OBJECT"

>> SKILL : THIEF
You throw something to victim. Damage depends on object's value and your level.
#
CAST

>> COMMAND
If you want to throw a spell at someone or something.

EXAMPLE :
	> cast 'burning hands' <player>

Note that the name of the spell must be enclosed by "'"s.

See also : help on each individual spell, for example :
	> help cure ligh
	> help ventri
	> help energy drain
