#
GRAB HOLD

>> COMMAND
For getting a good grip on something; a torch, for example.

See also : WEAR, WIELD, REMOVE
#
FOLLOW

>> COMMAND
If you happen to be going in the same direction as someone else, why not simply
follow that person? For example, "Follow joe". If you are following someone
and you wish to stop doing that, then all you've got to do is follow yourself,
"follow <your name>".

See also : GROUP, SOLO
#
SOLO

>> COMMAND
If you dislike someone follows you, just type "solo".
It's a toggle command.

See also : FOLLOW
#
FLEE

>> COMMAND
If you are in a fight and things are beginning to get a little uncomfortable
(maybe your are dying), just type 'flee', and presto! you are out of harm's way
- that is, IF there is a suitable exit nearby, and IF that exit doesn't simply
bring you from the ashes to the fire... but then, who wants to live forever?
When you flee, you lost some exp. If victim's level is higher than you, you'll
lost more exp. (level difference effects on loss of exp significantly.)
#
IMPLEMENTOR GOD WIZARD

>> INFORMATION
The most powerful being in existence.
#
DICE

>> INFORMATION
dice(n, m) means n dices with m size(side). So, dice(3, 5) means average 9.
#
GUILD

>> INFORMATION
The Guildhouse is the place where mortals may go to escape the troubles and
perils of a cruel world. Each guild is heavily guarded, so that only members
may enter the building. Guilds are also the places where people come to
learn and practice the skills of their trade.

Currently following guilds are available :
	ASSASSIN, OUTLAW, POLICE

See also : ASSASSIN, OUTLAW, POLICE
#
ASSASSIN

>> INFORMATION
Assassin guild is a group of player who has evil mind. They earns money by PK.
They like red aura, and dark mood. They always have cold face.

See also : JOIN, SOLACE, SHADOW FIGURE, EVIL STRIKE, IMPROVED REFLECT DAMAGE
#
SOLACE

>> ASSASSIN GUILD SKILL
When you feel coming of death, you can return to guild immediately.

See also : SHADOW FIGURE, EVIL STRIKE, IMPROVED REFLECT DAMAGE
#
"SHADOW FIGURE"

>> ASSASSIN GUILD SKILL
You can make yourself to shadow, and other player can't see your real face.
And can't find where you are. When you make your shadow, your damage is
doubled with some luck.

See also : SOLACE, EVIL STRIKE, IMPROVED REFLECT DAMAGE
#
"EVIL STRIKE"

>> ASSASSIN GUILD SKILL
Your evil power makes critical damage on your victim. If victim is more evil
than you, you can't get a chance of success well. Otherwise, you will get
more change of success. Damage depends on your evil mind and level.
If your strike succeed, victim can't do anything for 1 round.
If you fail, your victim get some hit points.

See also : SOLACE, SHADOW FIGURE, IMPROVED REFLECT DAMAGE
#
"IMPROVED REFLECT DAMAGE"

>> ASSASSIN GUILD SKILL
When you are affected by reflect damage, you will reflect
dice(((level - 20) / 4 + 1), learned) more damage.

See also : SOLACE, SHADOW FIGURE, IMPROVED REFLECT DAMAGE
#
OUTLAW

>> INFORMATION
Outlaw guild is a group of player who has chaotic mind. They usually drink,
smoke, assault and do many harmful things to others.

See also : JOIN, ANGRY YELL, ASSAULT, SMOKE, INJECT, CHARGE
#
"ANGRY YELL"

>> OUTLAW GUILD SKILL
With your angry yell, victim is frightened, and get damage.
Damage depends on your con + str + dex - int - wis, level difference, and
how much you learned. If succeed, you will damage victim and get some
hit points of victim. But if fail, you will get some damage.

See also : ASSAULT, SMOKE, INJECT, CHARGE
#
ASSAULT

>> OUTLAW GUILD SKILL
Just do it! And See What Happend!

See also : ANGRY YELL, SMOKE, INJECT, CHARGE
#
SMOKE

>> OUTLAW GUILD SKILL
Sorry. Not implemented.

See also : ANGRY YELL, ASSAULT, INJECT, CHARGE
#
INJECT

>> OUTLAW GUILD SKILL
Sorry. Not implemented.

See also : ANGRY YELL, ASSAULT, SMOKE, CHARGE
#
CHARGE

>> OUTLAW GUILD SKILL
Charge is outlaw guild's most powerful skill. Damage depends on your
hit + mana + move points. But if fails, you will be damaged as much as
victim's move points. If succeed, you can't do anything for 2 round.
If fail, you can't do anything for 1 round.

See also : ANGRY YELL, ASSAULT, SMOKE, INJECT
#
POLICE

>> INFORMATION
Police guild is a group of player who has good mind. They caught bad guys.

See also : JOIN, BROADCAST, SIMULTANEOUS, ARREST, POWER BASH
#
BROADCAST

>> POLICE GUILD SKILL
Broadcast is useful skill. When you broadcast, where the victim is is known
to all police guild member. And victim is know as criminal person.
Criminal person is attacked by all guard until he die.

See also : SIMULTANEOUS, ARREST, POWER BASH
#
SIMULTANEOUS

>> POLICE GUILD SKILL
Simultaneous attack is most powerful skill for police guild. If simultaneous
attack succeed, all police member in same room will attack victim. And attacker
can't do anything for 1/3 round. So does victim. Damage depends on attacker's
int and how much he learned.

See also : BROADCAST, ARREST, POWER BASH
#
ARREST

>> POLICE GUILD SKILL
When victim is wounded, you can arrest him. And send him to prison.

See also : BROADCAST, SIMULTANEOUS, POWER BASH
#
POWER BASH

>> POLICE GUILD SKILL
Like bash, but more powerful than bash. You and victim can't do anything for
maximum 4 rounds.

See also : BROADCAST, SIMULTANEOUS, ARREST
#
CANT

>> GUILD COMMAND
Like gtell, talk with all guild member.
#
JOIN

>> COMMAND
You can join any guild you want (with some level restriction).
You can only use this command in front of guild entrance.
To join any guild, type JOIN (capital letter).
When you want to leave your guild, then type LEAVE (capital letter).
#
TRAIN

>> GUILD COMMAND
Like practice, but only to guild member.

See also : PRACTICE
#
WHERE

>> COMMAND
Tells you the location of a monster, a player, a object (for GOD).

EXAMPLE :
	> where torch
	> where dragon

Mortals can only "where" monsters or players, and only from their own zone.
Immortals may type 'where' without arguments to see where everybody is.
#
USERS

>> COMMAND
For mortals, show how many people are playing (and visible), and also
the maximum number of players since last game restart.  For immortals,
tells you who's logged on to the game, and where they are playing from.
#
LEVELS

>> COMMAND
Lists the levels of your class. 
#
BRIEF

>> COMMAND
Toggle "brief mode". When in brief mode, you don't see the descriptions of the
room you are in; only the name of the room, and the people and objects in
there. Unless you are very familiar with the area in which you travel, however,
it is not advisable to use this command. Frequently, you will find small, but
vital hints in the descriptions of the rooms: An extra peek at your
surroundings could mean the difference between life and death!

See also : COMPACT
#
! !!

>> COMMAND
Repeat the last command typed at the keyboard.
You can also use like "!c" to repeat last c-first command.

EXAMPLE :
	> cast 'detect inv'
	You lost your concentration!
	> ! (!! or !c works also)
	Ok.
	Your eyes tingle.
#
CONSIDER

>> COMMAND

USAGE :
	consider <monster>

This command will compare your Level with the <monsters> level. You will then
receive a rough estimate, which is by no means exact. Consider does not take
hitpoints/special attacks/damage into accout.

See also : QUERY
#
QUERY

>>  GUILD COMMAND
This command is better than consider but, you must join any guild to use this.
#
"ARMOR CLASS" AC

>> INFORMATION
In original diku, armor class is only related with hit or miss. But in this
world, armor class is very significant. Armor class is related with hit or
miss no more. Hit or miss is just depends on your class, level and dex.
When you are hit, the lower ac, the less damage. Armor class has no limit.
#
EXPERIENCE XP

>> INFORMATION
Whenever you kill a monster or a player, you earn experience points. When
enough experience points are earned, you raise a level.
Things you should know about experience points:

  * When damaging a monster, you get experience points.

  * If you kill a monster of higher level than yourself, you get bonus
    experience points. If killing a monster of lower level you'll gain
    less experience points

  * When you are in group, group's gaining XP is calculated like this.
      mob's exp
    + (number of "equivalent" level players in same room - 1) * mob's half exp 
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------
    = total exp

      total exp
    / number of group member
    / highest level in group
    ------------------------
    = shared exp

      shared exp
    * one's level
    -------------
    = exp gained

    "equivalent" level means difference with highest level is smaller than 5. 

We encourage killing of other players, but the choice is yours.

See Also : GROUP
#
GROUP

>> COMMAND

USAGE :
	 group [player]

If you are a group member, then you will share experience points for killing
monsters equally among the group. Experience points will only be shared among
group members that are in the same location, at the time of the killing
blow. Sharing is regardless of wherther the group members have been
participating in the fight.

Group with no argument show a list of people with whom you are grouped.

To make a group, a "leader" must be selected. All members of the group
must then "follow" the leader using the follow command. The leader should
NOT follow anyone at all! The leader can now toggle group membership for
each player in the group, by using "group <player_name>". The leader
should remember to include himself in the group.

EXAMPLE :
	Ares and Process wishes to group with Dragon.
	Process> follow ares
	Dragon> follow ares
	(Ares should be following no one but himself)
	Ares> group ares
	Ares> group process
	Ares> group dragon

Later when Ares get upset at Process (because he is sleeping all the time)
he types : "group process" to kick Process out of the group.

See Also : XP EXPERIENCE
#
